<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">I'm 54 and I still do the things I did at 30.  Crowd control, buff and every now and then a little damage.<P>It all really depends on what you are doing.  If you are doing a Vox raid you are extremely important with mana sieve.  If you are doing a raid on some other mobs that are completely immune to magic then you are stuck at just being a buffer.<P>You will still do alot of crowd control in high level dungeons and planes...if anything enchanters are even more essential for dungeons at higher level for crowd control.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Llorian
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Depends on what your guild does, and what you consider to be " high level"..<P>I am 56, and i still consider that to be "mid - high level".. to me " high level" is 59 or 60.<P>If you are an enchanter for a raid based guild, on MANY of the raids you will be a buffer.<P>If you are an enchanter in a guild that doesnt do ubermobs, you can get to 60 doing the same things you are basically doing at 30.. it doesnt change too much, only the mobs hit harder so you have less margin for error.<P>Most enchanters in the " end game" end up being buffers, because the "end game" for a lot of folks is about taking down the large mobs in the game.  Even in this regard, the level 60 enchanter with dictate can be a powerful force if there are mobs close by they can dictate onto the main mob.<P>I would say that the enchanters highlight of his career is from 20-57 ish, and after that we tend to become more buffers than crowd control specialists, depending on what you do.<P>That is a LONG time to be powerful, and given the average rate of play for people will take most quite some time.<P>Llorian<BR>56 enchanter</FONT>
</TD></TR>

