<TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Tudamorf
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">Llorian says:  <i>I would say that the enchanters highlight of his career is from 20-57 ish, and after that we tend to become more buffers than crowd control specialists, depending on what you do.<P>That is a LONG time to be powerful</i><P>Actually, I would make the distinction between large single-target raids and single groups.  Enchanters are almost always extremely functional in a single group, regardless of level.  Even at level 60 there are plenty of challenges for single group that require a competent enchanter.<P>In large single-target raids, enchanters often having a buffing role.  However, a boring role is not necessarily a less powerful one.  Enchanters provide the single most important buff in most raids:  haste.  Without haste, many of the feats accomplished by today's players would be impossible with the configurations they presently use.  Most enchanters take haste for granted (like clarity), but if you've ever tried to function without it, you know how painful it can be.<P>In addition, as you said, enchanters often have ancillary roles in some raids, such as incredible damage dealing with charm, or prevention of damage with Rune.<P>Overall, enchanters are quite powerful, and I disagree with your characterization of a decline in power after level 57.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#F7F7F7">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Goshan
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">When Velious first came out, I stated that enchanters had been relegated to buffers at the highest levels of the game. This opinion comes from someone in a raid guild capable of doing any mob. Since we have conquered most of those mobs, my view has changed. We are still primarily buffers and do a superb job at it. As Tudamorf points out, most raids would be impossible without the Haste we provide tanks and clarity we provide casters. <P>However, there are now many raids where charm tactics are REQUIRED unless you plan on doing a zergling rush of 60 people on a particular mob. Sure you can do Dain with 50 people. But try it with 25-30. You will want 3 or 4 enchanters along to help out with the fight. There is even talk of being able to do the baddest mob of them all, The Avatar of Rallos Zek. That simply would not be possible without charmed giants tanking the whole battle. Charm tactics have come into their own with Velious. We even had an encounter up until last patch where we could solo a lvl 65 Giant. The only place my guild does not use charm now is where mobs dispel which makes it almost useless(still working on tactics to get around this).</FONT>
</TD></TR>

<TR bgcolor="#DEDFDF">
<TD valign=top>
<FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">
Yana
</FONT></TD>
<TD><FONT SIZE="2" FACE="Verdana, Arial">""However, there are now many raids where charm tactics are REQUIRED unless you plan on doing a zergling rush of 60 people on a particular mob. Sure you can do Dain with 50 people. But try it with 25-30. You will want 3 or 4 enchanters along to help out with the fight. There is even talk of being able to do the baddest mob of them all, The Avatar of Rallos Zek. That simply would not be possible without charmed giants tanking the whole battle.""<P>Charm is never required. It helps to some degree, and better in certain places then others. <P>Dain is killable with 25 without using charm.<P>Do you mean Avatar of War? Well I wouldn't say he is impossible without using charm. He is prob the hardest hitting mob to date. Quad 1045 with flurries averaging every 3 rounds of attack at nearly 0 delay. I believe he is possible to defeat using the right tactics, without charming, to kill. <P>Fjokar was one of the very vew exceptions where an enc can utilize and dish out a ridiculous amount of dmg making it almost an exploit. VI was doing the right thing to make him over the charm cap. A quad 600, flurry, backstabing mob should never be a tool used by players in an uber encounter. While the method is clever, it undermines the accomplishments of the rest of the raid party. People have brought 40 to engage Tormax and killed him without using Fjokar. That is more of an accomplishment then going with 35 and using 5-6 lvl 60 Enc to get Fjokar to do more then half the dmg during the encounter. <P>For most cases, charming a dual 250-300 hitting mob helps, but so is the crucial rune on the primary tank that allows a Complete Heal to land in time. Nothing is required, you choose to do what ever you think can contribute more, provided that you can deal with the consequences, charm break and rune aggro.</FONT>
</TD></TR>

